longBusinessSummary: Paxman AB (publ), together with its subsidiaries, develops and sells Paxman scalp cooling system to minimize hair loss in connection with chemotherapy treatment worldwide. It serves various cancer centers and hospitals. The company has collaborated with the University of Huddersfield and the University of Leeds to utilize state-of-the-art technological advances to develop a wearable medical cooling device, and the National University Hospital of Singapore for the development of a cooling and compression system. Paxman AB (publ) was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in Karlshamn, Sweden.
